<br>
I read the links and other sources discussing Hapgood's theory. His origonal theory was based on old maps which he believed showed an ice free Antartica. His interpitations are suspect at best. There are also several problems for his theory that sudden poleshifts cause ice ages. Europe, North America, and Asia all suffered equally from encroching ice sheets, indicitive that the pole was much where it is Today, not shifted towards N.A.. Plate techtonics was not widely supported until magnetic studies in the 1960's showed seafloor spreading. It explains most of the geological processes Hapgood attributed to poleshifting. <p>&quot;If,&quot; he wispered, &quot;if we could only pick that lock....&quot; - , THE WORLD SET FREE</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showMessageRange?topicID=24.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showPrevMessage?topicID=24.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showNextMessage?topicID=24.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=29><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/addreply3.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.emailToFriend?topicID=24.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.threadControl?topicID=24.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/space/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.subscribeUnre